Top Skills Required in Data Scientist / Analytics Roles
Most In-Demand Skills
Based on the analysis of the provided CSV file, the following are the top skills most frequently required in data scientist and analytics roles:

Python

SQL

R

Tableau

AWS

Spark

Java

Azure

Pandas

Hadoop

These skills appear most often in job postings for data scientist and analytics positions, highlighting their importance in the current job market.



Key Takeaways
Python and SQL are by far the most sought-after skills, appearing in the majority of job postings.

Visualization and cloud skills such as Tableau and AWS are also highly valued.

Proficiency in multiple programming languages (e.g., R, Java) and big data tools (Spark, Hadoop) is a strong asset.

Skills in cloud platforms (AWS, Azure) and data manipulation libraries (Pandas) are increasingly important.